  "settingsAntiPhishingDialogTitle": "Anti-phishing",
  "settingsAntiPhishingDialogBody": "Pass Tech can verify that the foreground browser is on the entry's domain BEFORE copying your password. If the domain does not match (typosquatting, fake site), an alert is shown.\n\nFor this, the app uses an Android accessibility service:\n• Reads only the root domain from the URL bar\n• Only on supported browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Brave, Edge, Opera, Vivaldi, Samsung, DuckDuckGo)\n• No data stored or transmitted — volatile memory only\n• Can be disabled at any time in Android Settings\n\nOn the next screen, enable \"Pass Tech — anti-phishing\".",
